docs.abstract: Profit-sharing plans for rank-and-file employees are vanishing as corporate America has adopted a new approach toward who reaps a healthy company’s gains.
docs.snippet: Profit-sharing plans for rank-and-file employees are vanishing as corporate America has adopted a new approach toward who reaps a healthy company’s gains.
docs.lead_paragraph: Half a century ago, a typical Sears salesman could walk out of the store at retirement with a nest egg worth well over a million in today’s dollars, feathered with company stock. A warehouse worker hired now at Amazon who stays until retirement would leave with a fraction of that.

headline.main: When Sears Flourished, So Did Workers. At Amazon, It’s More Complicated.
headline.print_headline: In Its Heyday, Sears Spread the Wealth. Companies Today Don’t.

docs.lead_paragraph: On the Tuesday episode of her show, Megyn Kelly made remarks on blackface Halloween costumes that caused a backlash. On Wednesday, she looked into the camera and apologized. docs.abstract: In 1968, feminists threw bras and girdles into a trash can to protest the Miss America pageant for sexism. Now, #MeToo may have finally ushered in a new era.
docs.snippet: In 1968, feminists threw bras and girdles into a trash can to protest the Miss America pageant for sexism. Now, #MeToo may have finally ushered in a new era.
docs.lead_paragraph: Fifty years ago, the swimsuit-wearing beauties of the Miss America pageant were confronted with a spectacle on the Atlantic City boardwalk: 100 feminists throwing bras, girdles, curling irons, false eyelashes and other “instruments of female torture” into a trash can labeled “Freedom.”

headline.print_headline: Miss America Scraps Swimsuits, Making Strides to Reshape Image

docs.lead_paragraph: FALLBROOK, Calif. — After flames rolled over the hills north of San Diego and engulfed vineyards, avocado groves and neighborhoods, hundreds in this area were left with only the charred remains of homes and businesses.
